<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 11:46AM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...SEVERE THUNDERSTORMS ARE POSSIBLE THIS AFTERNOON AND EVENING
ACROSS SOUTHERN NEW ENGLAND...
Severe thunderstorms, with damaging wind and large hail, are
possible across southern New England this afternoon and evening.
The main threat will be between 2 PM and 10 PM. In addition, an
isolated tornado cannot be ruled out. Heavy downpours may cause
localized flooding.
Skywarn weather spotters should be prepared to relay reports of
severe weather to the National Weather Service.
Stay tuned to the latest weather information and listen for severe
weather watches and warnings. Remember, when thunder roars, go
indoors. There is no safe place outdoors when lightning is
striking.</description>
